DataType\u0022 as UniqueIdentifier, and \u0022DefaultValue\u0022 highlighted as \u0022Status_New.\u0022 Additional fields indicate \u0022DefaultLookup\u0022 as \u0022Status_Name_GetId,\u0022 \u0022Mapped Column Name\u0022 is \u0022Status,\u0022 and \u0022Mapped Data Type\u0022 categorized as Misc. Other properties include options like \u0022ExcludeFromAuditing\u0022 and \u0022IsPrimaryKey,\u0022 both marked as False. The apparent purpose is to detail the schema settings for the \u0022Status_Id\u0022 field within a database configuration interface.\n\n\n  \n Save your changes, restart the Docker container with your server, and in the client application, your drop-down menu will display the default value you set: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/a/a30bebf76ae2f244ae392eed7db25e73e33a8f57.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a user interface for a task management system labeled \u0022Tasks.\u0022 It includes a section titled \u0022Task\u0022 with fields for \u0022Name,\u0022 \u0022Description,\u0022 \u0022Assigned to,\u0022 \u0022DueDate,\u0022 \u0022Priority,\u0022 and \u0022Status.\u0022 The \u0022Status\u0022 field currently displays the value \u0022New\u0022 within a dropdown menu, suggesting a selection option. The layout allows users to input details for tasks, indicating the system\u2019s purpose is to organize and manage task-related information effectively.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:49:38"},"vector":[-0.039607182,-0.039854042,-0.07654778,-0.0037763934,-0.022486368,-0.03436119,0.0070940233,0.011202675,0.005982098,0.016090877,-0.03561403,0.0012675253,0.00423058,0.032877684,0.030657668,0.013425974,0.007011704,0.014971081,-0.0018986845,0.046088167,-0.013184988,-0.023688607,0.032672487,0.009150421,-0.016840465,0.027533319,0.011822249,-0.03326042,-0.034439933,0.03238926,0.0334566,-0.041973807,-0.012465506,-0.039067768,-0.0037900407,-0.0198